            "file_path": "/Users/jserv/playground/threadx-cortex-r5-demo/CHANGELOG.md",
            "new_string": "# CHANGELOG: ThreadX Cortex-R5 Improvements\n\nThis document tracks completed improvements and their implementation details.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-25\n\n### [P1-Z1] ZynqMP GIC Interrupt Handling + Context Save Fix\n**Status**: RESOLVED (100% pass rate: 110/110 ZynqMP, 20/20 VersatileAB)\n\n**Problem**: ZynqMP (xlnx-zcu102) had two classes of failures:\n1. GIC deferred EOI race: Level-triggered TTC interrupt re-triggered between EOIR and CPSID\n2. Callee-saved register corruption: `r4` clobbered in `tx_thread_context_save.S`\n\n**Root Cause (r4 clobber)**: The SVC/SYS mode-switching code (commit `b0c54c61` in sysprog21/threadx fork) used `r4` as scratch to determine the interrupted thread's processor mode. `r4` is callee-saved but NOT part of the minimal interrupt frame (r0-r3, r10, r12, PC, CPSR). When the thread resumed via the no-preempt restore path, `r4` was silently corrupted. This caused ~5% intermittent \"FIFO order broken\" and \"counter mismatch\" panics depending on whether the compiler had a live value in `r4` at the interrupt point.\n\n**Fix**: Replace `r4` with `r0` at three clobber sites in `tx_thread_context_save.S`:\n1. Mode-bit extraction (`AND`/`CMP` for SVC vs SYS check)\n2. CPSR switch (`MOV`/`MSR` for SYS_MODE and SVC_MODE)\n3. IRQ mode re-entry (`MOV`/`MSR` for IRQ_MODE after saving context)\n\n`r0` is safe because it is overwritten by `LDMIA r2,{r0-r3}` before being saved, and at the IRQ re-entry point `r0` has had its last use as the thread pointer.\n\n**Deferred EOI Implementation** (ThreadX upstream `TX_GIC_DEFERRED_EOI`):\n- `tx_initialize_low_level.S`: Read GICC_IAR at IRQ entry, store in `_tx_gic_iar`\n- `tx_thread_context_restore.S`: Write GICC_EOIR after CPSID, invalidate IAR to 0x3FF\n- `gic.rs`: `current_irq_id()` reads `_tx_gic_iar` via volatile for Rust dispatch\n- `build.rs`: Defines `TX_GIC_DEFERRED_EOI=1`, `TX_GIC_CPU_INTERFACE_BASE=0xF9020000`\n\n**ZynqMP Platform Support Added**:\n- Board feature: `--features zynqmp` with Cadence UART, TTC timer, GIC drivers\n- `config_zynqmp.rs`: Hardware memory map (GICD 0xF901_0000, GICC 0xF902_0000, TTC, UART)\n- `gic.rs`: GIC distributor + CPU interface driver with lockstep-only constraints\n- `cadence_ttc.rs`: Triple Timer Counter driver with prescaler and interval mode\n- `cadence_uart.rs`: Cadence UART driver with emergency write for fault handlers\n- `startup.rs`: SCTLR.V clearing for low vectors (ZynqMP R5 boots with high vectors)\n- `linker_zynqmp.ld`: Memory layout for RPU (vectors at 0x0, DDR at 0x100000)\n- Makefile: `make BOARD=zynqmp` / `make BOARD=zynqmp run`\n\n**Compile-Time Constraints** (build.rs):\n- `zynqmp` + `tx_enable_irq_nesting` -> compile_error (per-nesting IAR not implemented)\n- `zynqmp` + `smp` -> compile_error (global `_tx_gic_iar` not safe for SMP)\n\n**QEMU**: Requires patched Xilinx QEMU fork at `vendor/xilinx-qemu/` with RPU GIC wiring, TTC interrupt targets, and boot-cpu support. Upstream QEMU does not deliver interrupts to R5 cores.\n\n**Files (threadx fork)**:\n- `tx_thread_context_save.S`: r4 -> r0 fix (commit `27af123c`)\n- `tx_thread_context_restore.S`: GIC deferred EOI block (commit `df1ed08b`)\n- `example_build/tx_initialize_low_level.S`: Reference GIC init (commit `df1ed08b`)\n\n**Files (demo)**:\n- `cortex-r5-sample/Cargo.toml`, `build.rs`, `linker_zynqmp.ld`\n- `cortex-r5-sample/src/`: `lib.rs`, `main.rs`, `startup.rs`, `tx_initialize_low_level.S`\n- `cortex-r5-sample/src/`: `gic.rs`, `cadence_ttc.rs`, `cadence_uart.rs`, `config_zynqmp.rs`\n- `cortex-r5-sample/src/`: `buffered_uart.rs`, `exception.rs` (board-agnostic refactor)\n- `Makefile`, `cortex-r5-sample/Makefile`, `README.md`\n\n**Review**: Gemini confirmed correctness on all 5 register liveness points. Codex confirmed all 7 review points (PHONY, BOARD pattern, stack arithmetic, mode constants, no remaining callee-saved clobbers).\n\n---",
